# Service Implementations Style

- Implement service interfaces in `services/impl` and annotate classes with `@Service`.
- Use constructor injection and keep collaborators as class fields.
- Keep CRUD methods direct and repository-backed (`findAll`, `find`, `save`, `delete`, `exists`).
- Return `Optional<T>` from lookup methods where absent state is expected upstream.
- Keep orchestration logic in services for user/cart/purchase mutations and cross-repository operations.
- Prefer readable imperative loops and guard clauses for collection mutation flows.
- Keep token/auth logic in auth service implementations; controllers should call service entry points.
